&lt;div&gt;The Performance Assessment Engineer supports the analysis and evaluation of system performance for the program. This role focuses on developing analysis tools, assessing system behavior, and partnering with cross-functional teams to translate findings into actionable improvements.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY OF ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop software tools for ad-hoc post-processing analysis and visualization of system performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track program development updates and analyze results to detect regressions following code changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform in-depth performance analysis using Technical Performance Metrics (TPMs), Special Interest Items (SIIs), and other defined measures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate system performance across parameters such as timing, track quality, discrimination accuracy, and related metrics using large datasets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to conduct deep-dive performance investigations&lt;/li&gt;

